class:: ConvDifusserCh
summary:: Stereo convolution diffuser based on chowdsp_utils
categories:: UGens>Effects
related:: Guides/ChowDSPPorts

Description::

ConvDifusserCh follows the `ConvolutionDiffuser` design used in chowdsp reverbs. The kernel is generated from shaped noise, truncated by the requested diffusion time, scaled by the original `32 / sqrt(N)` law, and then applied through a partitioned convolution engine. In DSP terms this is not a room simulator by itself; it is a transient-smearing stage that redistributes energy across a short impulse response so later feedback or reverb stages receive a denser excitation.

That makes it useful anywhere a source feels too point-like or too dry before entering a larger reverb structure. Short settings act like a soft spatial blur, while longer settings start to create a grainier, more obviously clouded onset that can help synthetic drums, plucks, and clicks sit deeper in a mix.

definitionlist::
## diffusionTime: || diffusion time in milliseconds, practical range `10..1000`
::

